Subject: =?UTF-8?q?feat(slayzone):=20extensions=20modal=20=E2=80=94=20chro?=
 =?UTF-8?q?meless=20inlay=20pinned=20under=20a=20React=20card?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the detached extension-management window with a real SlayZone modal:
the React shell draws the scrim/card/header, and the Web Store renders in a
chromeless child browser "inlay" pinned over the card's body rect.

- SlayzoneInlayBrowserView: a chromeless BrowserView. The tab strip region is a
  DIRECT child of BrowserView (added last so it paints on top) — a sibling of
  top_container, not inside it — so it's hidden on its own, alongside
  top_container (toolbar/bookmark). contents_container fills the window. The Web
  Store stays the normal ACTIVE tab so install prompts/autofill anchor as in
  stock Chrome.
- BrowserNativeWidgetMac (gated on kExtensionsBrowserMarker): kFrameless (no
  traffic lights, mirrors document-PiP), rounded corners (12) + translucent, no
  window open/close animation, non-movable NSWindow; can_resize=false via
  CreateParams so the user can't drag or resize it.
- Host: open the inlay as a child of the shell window (Widget::Reparent) pinned
  to the React card's body rect (BodyToScreen: CSS px → screen DIPs via the
  container origin). SetExtensionsBounds tracks modal move/resize; CloseExtensions
  tears it down; the Store|Manage switch navigates the inlay's active tab.

Verified live: locked (no move/resize), instant (no anim), rounded, chrome-free.
